snippet: In stepping down, Arvind Kejriwal said his central anticorruption initiative was being stonewalled by legislators from two well-established parties.
abstract: Arvin Kejriwal, protest leader who was vaulted into the top post of Delih's government after a startling electoral victory, resigns from his seat after just 49 days in office, saying his central anticorruption initiative was being stonewalled by India's two well-established parties.

byline.original: By ELLEN BARRY and MALAVIKA VYAWAHARE

lead_paragraph: In stepping down, Arvind Kejriwal said his central anticorruption initiative was being stonewalled by legislators from two well-established parties.

headline.main: Chief Minister of Delhi Resigns After 49 Days, Citing Resistance to Antigraft Bill
headline.print_headline: Chief Minister of Delhi Resigns After 49 Days, Citing Resistance to Antigraft Bill
